{
  "stem": "16790.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She said she could not talk about it because it was too-- too emotionally draining for her.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She couldn't talk-- she never told me about my father's death.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I found that out from my cousin, Hans [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Achenhold ?] home from Kansas City.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my sister made a tape and my son heard the tape.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have not heard the tape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that's the information I have was from that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember my father-- his death because there was a tremendous amount of crying and carrying on and I had no idea what was going on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in Munich, my governess told me that my father was no longer alive, that he had died.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But nobody-- and I thought he had been killed in a concentration camp for years and I did not know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother sort of let me believe that until I just recently found out about this tape and this conversation that my cousin, Hans, had with my sister.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was-- it was probably closer to 10 days we were sitting in the harbor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then-- then the captain tried to get us to Miami.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got up to Miami and we saw-- and I remember seeing the automobiles on the causeway and looking at the-- at the hotels, the buildings.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I thought, wow, this is-- looks like a really nice place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then the-- a Coast Guard cutter drove us off and we could not enter, not even get close enough so that somebody could jump in-- into the water and swim toward-- towards land.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just drove us right off and we had to turn right around and go back to Havana and sat there for a couple more-- well, a couple of more days.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
